Absolutely, I have a custom ToolNode that represents our various internal services and exposes multiple endpoints as MCP tools. To do that I have one node in my workflow per service and then internally represent all endpoints as a `Toolkit` (non working example to demonstrate our approach):

```typescript
import { Toolkit } from 'langchain/agents';
import { DynamicTool, StructuredToolInterface } from '@langchain/core/tools';

export class TopicToolkit extends Toolkit {
        ...
	constructor(path: string, apis: Apis) {
		super();
		this.tools = Object.entries(topics).map(([name, definition]) => {
			return new DynamicTool({
				name,
				description: definition.description,
				func: async (args) => {...},
			});
		});
	}
}
```

I create this toolkit in `supplyData`:

```typescript
          async supplyData(this: ISupplyDataFunctions, itemIndex: number): Promise<SupplyData> {
		const path = this.getNodeParameter('path', itemIndex) as string;
		return {
			response: new TopicToolkit(path, await getApis(path)),
		};
	}
```

